  <article class="article">
    <p class="eyebrow">B2B sourcing guide</p>
    <h1>How to Choose a Reliable Tape Measure Manufacturer in China</h1>
    <p>Choosing a tape measure manufacturer is not only about unit price. Importers need a supplier that can confirm specifications, prepare samples, manage packaging details, and keep quality stable before shipment.</p>
    <h2>Review factory capability first</h2>
    <p>Ask what tape measure types the supplier regularly produces, including shell sizes, tape lengths, blade finishes, hooks, clips, and packaging styles. A reliable factory should be able to explain which options are standard and which require extra development.</p>
    <h2>Confirm customization details</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Logo position and printing method</li>
      <li>Shell color and material</li>
      <li>Tape length and blade coating</li>
      <li>Hook style and belt clip option</li>
      <li>Blister card, color box, display box, or private-label packaging</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Check quality control process</h2>
    <p>For B2B orders, the supplier should plan inspection points for raw materials, production, finished goods, packaging, and pre-shipment checks. This helps reduce mistakes before products leave the factory.</p>
    <h2>Look for clear communication</h2>
    <p>A strong supplier responds with practical questions about quantity, market, packaging, target price, and lead time. This is often a sign that the factory understands importer requirements.</p>
  </article>
  <CTA title="Need a reliable tape measure manufacturer?" primaryLabel="Send Your RFQ" />
